President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Tennessee due to severe storms, flooding, tornadoes, and straight-line winds that occurred on April 4, 2011. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. W. Montague Winfield has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA.